The Bruins lost their season opener against the Panthers, leading to criticism from the team's coach, Jim Montgomery. Trotz a loss, veteran forward Craig Smith remains with the Bruins, awaiting an opportunity. The Providence Bruins announced their opening night roster. name: Trump town hall
summary: At a town hall in Pennsylvania, President Trump unexpectedly spent around 39 minutes swaying and dancing to music after two attendees fainted. The incident, described as "bizarre" and "impromptu," occurred as the town hall was interrupted by medical emergencies in the crowd. Trump reportedly played his favorite music, including "Macho Man" by the Village People, for nearly half an hour, while attendees danced and waved their hands. The incident drew criticism from political opponents, with Vice President Kamala Harris expressing concern for Trump's well-being. The extended musical interlude ended the town hall, leaving some attendees confused and others expressing support for the president's unusual behavior.
